quran[18]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,97,"They said, "
  37,98,"And they intended for him a plan [i.e., harm], but We made them the most debased."
  37,99,"And [then] he said, "
  38,76,"He said, "
  38,77,"[Allāh] said, "
  38,78,"And indeed, upon you is My curse until the Day of Recompense."
  39,61,"And Allāh will save those who feared Him by their attainment;{1} no evil will touch them, nor will they grieve.",footnotes:1:[i.e., their success in the trials of worldly life and attainment of Paradise.]
  39,62,"Allāh is the Creator of all things, and He is, over all things, Disposer of affairs."
  39,63,"To Him belong the keys of the heavens and the earth. And they who disbelieve in the verses of Allāh - it is those who are the losers."
  40,40,"Whoever does an evil deed will not be recompensed except by the like thereof; but whoever does righteousness, whether male or female, while he is a believer - those will enter Paradise, being given provision therein without account."
  40,41,"And O my people, how is it that I invite you to salvation while you invite me to the Fire?"
  40,42,"You invite me to disbelieve in Allāh and associate with Him that of which I have no knowledge, and I invite you to the Exalted in Might, the Perpetual Forgiver.{1}",footnotes:1:[Refer to footnotes in 38:66.]
  41,19,"And [mention, O Muḥammad], the Day when the enemies of Allāh will be gathered to the Fire while they are [driven], assembled in rows,"
  41,20,"Until, when they reach it, their hearing and their eyes and their skins will testify against them of what they used to do."
  41,21,"And they will say to their skins, "
  42,4,"To Him belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is in the earth, and He is the Most High, the Most Great.{1}",footnotes:1:[See footnote to 2:255.]
  42,5,"The heavens almost break from above them,{1} and the angels exalt [Allāh] with praise of their Lord and ask forgiveness for those on earth. Unquestionably, it is Allāh who is the Forgiving, the Merciful.",footnotes:1:[i.e., from the grandeur of Allāh (subḥānahu wa taʿālā) above them.]
  42,6,"And those who take as allies other than Him - Allāh is [yet] Guardian over them; and you, [O Muḥammad], are not over them a manager."